The Associated Press reported that a Mets fan who pleaded guilty Tuesday to shining a high-powered flashlight at two Atlanta Braves players last month will be banned from Shea for three years.

“Frank Martinez, 40, of the Bronx, also must spend 15 days in jail as part of his sentence for interfering with a professional sporting event,” the AP reported.

“In a game in which the ball can travel upward of 110 mph, the defendant’s actions were dangerous to both spectators and players,” Queens District Attorney Richard Brown said in a statement.